<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Chapter 1: Introduction to HTML and CSS with (BONUS)</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet"href="cp1.css"type="text/css"> <!--External stylesheet-->
</head>
<body>
    

    <!--A h1 tag for the recipe name-->
    <h1>Binangkal</h1>
    

    <!--A p tag for a description of the recipe-->
    <i><p>Binangkal is a native doughnut from Mindanao and Visayas, 
        but also commonly found in most homegrown neighborhood bakeries 
        or panaderias in the Philippines.
    </p></i>

    
    <div class="recipe">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2><!--A h2 tag for the ingredients-->
        <ul class="ingredients">
            <!--An unorder list for the ingredients-->
            <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1/4 Cup cornstarch</li>
            <li>3/4 Cup white sugar</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon Salt</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon baking powder</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons salted butter melted</li>
            <li>1 large egg</li>
            <li>1/2 Cup evaporated milk</li>
            <li>1/2 Cup sesame seeds,</li>
            <li>1/4 teaspoon vanilla (Optional)</li>    

            <img src="Binangkal Recipe & How to Cook Guide.jpg" width="400px" height="300px">

        </ul>        
    </div>

    
    <div class="instruction">
    <h2>Method</h2> <!--An h2 tag for the method-->
    <ol class="ins2">
        <!--An order list for the steps involved in the recipe 'method'-->
        <li>Combine all dry ingredients in a bowl: flour, cornstarch, sugar, salt, and baking powder. Mix well.</li>
        <li>In a separate bowl mix together milk, melted butter, and egg. Mix well.</li>
        <li>Slowly add the dry ingredients into the wet mixture. Mix well to form a dough..</li>
        <li>Scoop a tablespoon mixture to form a ball and roll it into the sesame seeds..</li>
        <li>Prepare oil in a pan for deep frying. Make sure the oil is hot before putting the dough.</li>
        <li>Deep fry until golden brown.</li>
        
    </ol>
    
    <!--Video link for tutorial-->
        <h2>
            <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BQ6H4qb5VDM" class ="link">CLICK HERE FOR TUTORIAL </a>
        </h2>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
